-- BOJ says to keep providing sufficient funds to mkt
-- 
-- Tue Mar 11, 2008 9:31am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/11/us-japan-economy-boj-idUST25657720080311

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - The Bank of Japan said on Tuesday it would continue to conduct monetary market operations appropriately to maintain market stability, including sufficient funds over the fiscal year-end. 

 It also added that Group of 10 central banks have continued to work together closely and to consult regularly on liquidity pressure in funding markets. (Reporting by  Yoko Nishikawa ; Editing by  Rodney Joyce )